      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and rest the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the pastry-quantity {{unsalted-butter}} into {{plain-flour}} and {{icing-sugar}} until the mixture resembles fine crumbs. Add the pastry {{egg-yolks}} and 2 to 3 tablespoons of cold water; mix to a firm dough. Wrap and refrigerate for 60 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line and blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll the pastry to 3 mm thick and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin. Prick the base, line with baking paper, fill with baking beans, and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Heat the oven to 180°C fan (200°C conventional). Blind bake for 15 minutes, then remove the paper and beans and bake for a further 8 minutes until the base is lightly golden. Leave to cool slightly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Reduce the oven to 170°C fan. Whisk {{dark-brown-sugar}}, {{golden-syrup}}, the filling-quantity melted {{unsalted-butter}}, {{eggs}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} together until smooth. Scatter {{pecans}} over the base of the tart case. Pour the filling over them slowly; the pecans will float and arrange themselves. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until the filling is set at the edges and has a gentle wobble in the centre. It should read 85°C on a probe thermometer. Cool completely before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The filling sets further as it cools. A tart that wobbles in the centre at 30 minutes will be fully set after two hours at room temperature.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To add bourbon: stir 2 tablespoons into the filling with the vanilla. The alcohol bakes out; the flavour deepens the tart.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Toast the pecans in a dry pan for two minutes before adding them to the tart case; it intensifies their flavour noticeably.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
